    "updated_at": "2018-04-24T14:31:52Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Stumbled on this issue looking for a solution. The workaround I came up with is to execute the following in the notebook.\r\n```\r\nfrom IPython.core.display import display, HTML\r\ndisplay(HTML(\"<style>.rendered_html td { white-space: pre; }</style>\"))\r\n```\r\nA global alternative would be to add the corresponding CSS to your ipython/jupyter custom profile."
